# Sous Monorepo — Navigation & Boundaries

Sous is an npm-workspaces + Turborepo monorepo containing **two applications**
and **two shared packages**. Every agent session must treat these as four
distinct boundaries.

```
/ (repo root)
├── apps/
│   ├── web/       Next.js 16 dashboard  (managers / owners)
│   └── mobile/    Expo SDK 54 app       (staff / shift leads)
├── packages/
│   ├── config/    Shared Tailwind preset (web + mobile)
│   └── types/     Shared Zod schemas and DTO types (@sous/types)
├── solver/        Python FastAPI CP-SAT microservice (Docker)
├── docs/          Canonical architecture & history docs
├── scripts/       Seed and maintenance scripts (web-scoped)
└── setup-agent-envs.sh  Materializes per-app .env files (see bootstrap-env skill)
```

---

## Hard boundary rules

1. **Never edit a file outside of the app you were asked to change.**
   A request about "the schedule" is almost always the web app; a request
   about "the staff phone UI" is almost always the mobile app. If unclear,
   **ask** rather than edit both.

2. **`cd` into the correct app directory before running app-specific
   commands.**

   | Action | Run from |
   |-------|---------|
   | `next dev`, `next build`, `next lint`, `tsc --noEmit` for web | `apps/web` |
   | `expo start`, `expo prebuild`, `tsc --noEmit` for mobile | `apps/mobile` |
   | `npm install` (always) | repo root |
   | `turbo run …`, `npm run dev:web`, `npm run dev:mobile` | repo root |
   | Seed scripts (`scripts/seed-*.ts`) | repo root, via `npm run seed:*` |

   Do **not** run `npm install` inside an app — it will fight the workspace
   resolver and produce a nested `node_modules`.

3. **Env files are per-app.** The web app reads `apps/web/.env.local`
   (Next.js convention). The mobile app reads `apps/mobile/.env` (Expo
   convention). Both are generated by `./setup-agent-envs.sh` — see the
   `bootstrap-env` skill. Do **not** hand-edit them.

4. **Shared code goes in `packages/`, never in an app.**
   - Validation schemas, DTO types, and enums → `packages/types/` (imported
     as `@sous/types`).
   - Tailwind preset and design tokens → `packages/config/` (imported as
     `@sous/config/tailwind-preset`).
   - If you find yourself copying a type between `apps/web` and
     `apps/mobile`, that type belongs in `packages/types` instead.

5. **The Python solver is its own service.**
   Don't try to port CP-SAT logic into TypeScript. The web app talks to
   the solver over HTTP via `CP_SOLVER_URL`. See
   `apps/web/src/server/services/cp-solver.service.ts`.

