## Turborepo commands (from repo root)

```bash
npm run dev:web         # next dev on apps/web
npm run dev:mobile      # expo start on apps/mobile
npm run build           # build all workspaces (turbo cached)
npm run lint            # lint all workspaces
npm run typecheck       # tsc --noEmit in every workspace
```

Turbo scopes environment variables per task (see `turbo.json`), so these
commands see the correct per-app env without `cd`. Prefer them for CI-like
checks; use `cd apps/<app> && npm run <task>` for tight dev loops.

---

## Which app owns the task?

Ask yourself **"where does this code execute?"** before touching anything:

| Symptom / keyword | App | Why |
|-------------------|-----|-----|
| "server action", "Mongoose", "MongoDB", "webhook", "route.ts", "Clerk middleware" | `apps/web` | Server lives here |
| "Stripe checkout", "billing portal", "subscription" | `apps/web` | Stripe SDK is web-only |
| "AI chat", "proposal", "OpenAI", "CP-SAT", "schedule generation" | `apps/web` | Orchestrator + solver are web-only |
| "Expo", "NativeWind", "React Native", "tab navigator", "staff phone", "tokenCache" | `apps/mobile` | Expo client only |
| "shared Zod schema", "shared DTO", "validation lives in both apps" | `packages/types` | Cross-boundary |
| "design token", "Tailwind colour", "warm industrial palette" | `packages/config` + each app's `globals.css` | Preset + CSS vars |

When in doubt, **read before write** (see `01-cloud-agent-conduct.mdc`) and
ask the user to disambiguate.

---

## Directory ownership cheat sheet

**`apps/web/` (Next.js 16, App Router, Node runtime):**
- `src/app/` – routes, layouts, page-local `_components/`
- `src/app/api/` – Route Handlers (webhooks, AI streaming, billing **only**)
- `src/components/` – shared components (`ui/`, `shared/`, `ai-chat/`, `marketing/`)
- `src/server/actions/` – Server Actions (primary client→server path)
- `src/server/services/` – business logic + Mongoose access
- `src/server/models/` – Mongoose schemas (imported **only** by services)
- `src/lib/` – framework-agnostic helpers (`auth/`, `ai/`, `db.ts`, `safe-action.ts`)
- `src/lib/validations/` – web-local Zod schemas (prefer `@sous/types` when shared)
- `src/proxy.ts` – Clerk middleware (non-standard filename; see `web-nextjs` rule)

**`apps/mobile/` (Expo SDK 54, React Native 0.81):**
- `app/` – Expo Router routes (`(auth)/`, `(tabs)/`)
- `features/` – feature modules (`auth/`, `home/`, `schedule/`, `time-off/`, `exchange/`)
  - each contains `screens/`, `components/`, `api.ts`, sometimes `store.ts`
- `lib/` – mobile-only helpers (`api-client.ts`, theme, token cache)
- `global.css` – NativeWind theme (mirrors web CSS variables)

When you are asked to "add a feature to the app", always clarify which app
and then follow the relevant rule:

- `web-nextjs.mdc` + `web-server-actions.mdc` for `apps/web/**`
- `mobile-expo.mdc` for `apps/mobile/**`
- `shared-types.mdc` for anything under `packages/types/**`
- `web-ai-orchestrator.mdc` for anything under `apps/web/src/lib/ai/**` or
  `apps/web/src/app/api/ai/**`
